Is there anything that needs to be modified in the spec above to allow druid to compact it without issues?

There are some checks in AuthorizationUtils that check for bugs where the code authorizes a request multiple times:

```
    if (request.getAttribute(AuthConfig.DRUID_AUTHORIZATION_CHECKED) != null) {
      throw new ISE("Request already had authorization check.");
    }
```

Prior to this patch, UNSECURED_PATHS only contained paths that did not have authorization checks.

With this patch, this check would need to be adjusted so that these functions no-op when the path is already allowed through the unsecured paths config.

Perhaps `UnsecuredResourceFilter` could add a new flag that indicates the request was allowed through the unsecured paths configuration.

